<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>BambooCraftMC - Discord Apps Guide</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            background-color: #1e1f22;
            color: #ffffff;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #2e7d32;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 28px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h2 {
            border-bottom: 2px solid #2e7d32;
            padding-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .step {
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .step img {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 700px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: block;
            margin: 15px 0;
        }

        .step p {
            font-size: 18px;
        }

        video {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 700px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    BambooCraftMC - How to Use Discord Apps
</header>

<div class="container">

    <h2>PC Guide</h2>

    <div class="step">
        <h3>Step 1</h3>
        <p>Click on the Apps button in the bottom-right of the message area.</p>
        <img src="pcBtimg1.png" alt="Click the Apps button">
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h3>Step 2</h3>
        <p>Select the B-MC Earth app from the list.</p>
        <img src="pcBtimg2.png" alt="Click B-MC Earth app">
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h3>Step 3</h3>
        <p>Choose one of the displayed commands to run.</p>
        <img src="pcBtimg3.png" alt="Select a command">
    </div>

    <h2>Mobile Guide</h2>

    <div class="step">
        <p>Watch the video below to see how to use Discord Apps on mobile.</p>
        <video controls>
            <source src="MobileGuide.mp4" type="video/mp4">
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
        </video>
    </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>
